category: STATE FLAGS
category comment: 

clue: Not "E pluribus unum" but this national motto appears on the flags of Georgia & Mississippi

response: In God We Trust

clue: In 1992 this state replaced the words "The Sunshine State" on its flag with the words "The Mount Rushmore State"

response: South Dakota

clue: Representations of the North Star & this other night sky feature appear on Alaska's flag

response: the Big Dipper (Ursa Major)

clue: This state's flag features the frigate Raleigh, built in Portsmouth in 1776 & the first ship to fly the U.S. flag in a sea battle

response: New Hampshire

clue: This state's flag bears the words "Battle Born", referring to it becoming a state during the Civil War

response: Nevada

